extends layout


block css
  != css("index")


block js
  != js("index")


block content
  .container
    .sixteen.columns.clearfix
      .row#logo
        .sixteen.columns.alpha
          img(src="/img/roboto_icon.png", width="200", height="200")

      .row#robotFace
        .sixteen.columns.clearfix#eyes
          .six.columns.alpha#leftEye.eye.robotPart
            :markdown
              **ter·ra·pin (n.)**
              /ˈtɛrəpɪn/
            :markdown
              1. Any of several North American turtles of the family Emydidae, that live in fresh or brackish water: especially diamondback terrapin.
            :markdown
              *The diamondback terrapin has been the University of Maryland's official school mascot since 1932.*

          .four.columns.empty

          .six.columns.omega#rightEye.eye.robotPart
            :markdown
              **hack·er (n.)**
              /ˈhækər/
            :markdown
              1. One who makes innovative customizations or combinations of retail electronic and computer equipment.
              2. One who combines excellence, playfulness, cleverness, and exploration in performed activities.
          .clear


        .sixteen.columns#nose.robotPart
          :markdown
            Make awesome stuff.
            Meet fantastic people.
            Maybe even start a company.
            Hack with [us](https://www.facebook.com/groups/hackersofmaryland/).

      .sixteen.columns.omega
        .two.columns.empty.alpha
        .fourteen.columns.omega#mouth.robotPart
          :markdown
            We do three things:

            1. Campus hacks. Public works of [art] [1], maybe using technology.
            2. Hack nights. [Hacking] [2] and building stuff with electronics and code.
            3. Hackathon trips. Take a trip to another university and build [something] [3] in 24-48 hours.

            [1]: http://hacks.mit.edu/Hacks/by_year/2006/firetruck/ "IHTFP Hack Gallery: Fire Truck on the Great Dome"
            [2]: http://stallman.org/articles/on-hacking.html       "On Hacking - Richard Stallman"
            [3]: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m33PqhdDl0M         "PennApps Demos - ScratchTable"

        .clear
